st $N$ better than the dynamic Debye screening approximation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 21 Jun 2000 20:24:04 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 5 Jul 2000 20:54:04 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 9 Mar 2001 20:02:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-10-31"}
